VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to check out our AI film events page over at Curious Refuge. Okay, let\'s get to it. So, the first bit of news that I want to talk about is Runway Olive 2.0. This is essentially an update to'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Runway\'s existing Omni model that allows you to upload reference footage and edit that footage and get a result in return. Now, the thing that makes Olif 2.0 know really interesting is you have the'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ability to upload your footage and then find a frame that you want to edit and then you edit it using a tool like Nano Banana Pro to get the change to be exactly what you\'re looking for and then'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you run Olive to actually add the visual effects into your scene. This is a much faster and cost-effective way of making changes to your footage rather than just simply prompting for what you want to'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'change and having to see what the result is, which can be quite expensive and a bit hard to control. But I don\'t want you to listen to me talking about it. Let\'s hop into the tool and see for ourselves. To use Runway Olive 2.0, all'

[01:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you have to do is go to the Runway website here and let\'s select that apps button on the left side of the frame. And from here under video, we\'re going to select the edit studio. So from here,'

[01:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we\'re going to bring in our reference footage. [music] For our reference footage, which we got from art list, we\'re going to use this clip here of this woman walking through a salt flat'

